{
  "stem": "5810.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my-- my days and what I remember of this whole situation, that particular item, is-- is really a puzzlement to me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I could swear to today that my father was there to protect me-- and on our way to Switzerland, we were arrested.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he was not.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we were taken to [SIGHS] Malines, where we were-- Could you spell Malines?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "M-A-L-I-N-E-S.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Belgium.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[DRINKS] There we were-- I remember being hustled into Gestapo headquarters, and-- and an office of a Gestapo officer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All my brothers and my sister and my mother, we were still together at the time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember a very stark office-- just one desk in the middle of a room with a Gestapo officer, who-- we were all on one side of a wall facing this officer.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was going to question us-- or he did question us-- one by one.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was very interested in who had organized this-- this-- this escape and who had done the paperwork, and who these people were, and where they were and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So one by one, we were questioned and then searched.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But something, if anything can be funny about the war, happened.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was very funny, and saved our live later on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Is that all my brothers and sisters were all together next to each other on one side of the wall, and the person that was to search us for whatever we had-- because people were known, or Jews were known to have taken all their belongings, and whatever money they may have put together, that they came to Switzerland with them.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And at the time, they thought, my family thought, that the safest person to carry this would be me.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
